title: Fix CI coverage reports
body: Since moving to using TypeScript, the coverage reports either fail or are wrong. This needs to be fixed so we can go back to failing CI builds at a certain threshold (see #20).

title: Change to using TypeScript
body: App can be incrementally changed over to TypeScript. This is a nice to have and I'll probably look at this after first release.

title: Mobile: Get entire document as markdown
body: For desktop, we can get the selected text using HTML as the coercion type. It's unknown if this is available on the mobile version. If not, we need to investigate what coercion types are available and if we'll need an additional parser.

title: Mobile: Convert selected text to markdown
body: For desktop, we can get the selected text using HTML as the coercion type. It's unknown if this is available on the mobile version. If not, we need to investigate what coercion types are available and if we'll need an additional parser.

title: Online: Convert entire document to markdown
body: **Blocked as we need an OOXML to HTML parser.**

title: Online: Convert selected text to markdown
body: **Blocked as we need an OOXML to HTML parser.** For desktop, we can get the selected text using HTML as the coercion type. This isn't available using the online version of Word.

title: Desktop: Convert entire document to markdown
Add end-to-end tests for existing features
body: Existing set of features aren't covered by any functional tests. There should be some in place to help protect against regression.

title: Run end-to-end tests as part of CI
body:
- [ ] Set up Sauce Labs account for this repo
- [ ] Configure Travis to run the end-to-end tests with Sauce Labs

title: Add ability to run end-to-end tests
body:
- [ ] Create Gulp task(s) to run Protractor
- [ ] Add sample feature file / steps to confirm that Protractor can run correctly

Could use Jasmine or Cucumber to write the tests. Preference for Cucumber, but not sure having the tests written in Gherkin adds much value in this case.

title: Fail CI build if coverage is below threshold
body: Need to set an appropriate threshold value. Probably 90% per file.
